The station commander of the Groblersdal police station, Colonel Jeffery Seroka, has been shot and killed. Limpopo Police spokesperson Motlafela Mojapelo spoke to Gareth Edwards. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The station commander of the Groblersdal police station, Colonel Jeffery Seroka, has been shot and killed.
He was leaving for a funeral when he was confronted in front of his home in Maganasebusa village at around 4.30am. The motive for his killing is not known and police are still investigating. Seroka's bakkie was taken and was later found abandoned. Limpopo police spokesperson Motlafela Mojapelo said a manhunt has been launched for the murder suspects. "As he walked out of his house he was shot dead in front of his gate," Mojapelo said. "We are currently investigating all possibilities."